text:

(Photo: Matt Olsen, KVUE) CONNECT 2   With just more than two weeks to go until the festival, Fun Fun Fun Fest has announced set times for the 10th annual festival and official FFF Nites shows. 
Gates open at noon daily at Auditorium Shores from Nov. 6-8, and headliners will perform on the Orange Stage nightly, with Chvrches headlining Friday, Jane's Addiction on Saturday and D'Angelo and the Vanguard closing out the fest Sunday night. 
Nites shows will take place at The Mohawk, The Sidewinder, The Parish, Cheer Up Charlie's, Beerland, ACL Live and more downtown locales. Many Nites events are free with a festival wristband, but some require tickets or RSVPs. 
Organizers are offering festivalgoers the opportunity to pick up festival tickets in person at the offsite "Funderdome," located at 908 East Fifth Street #106c and open from 10 a.m. to 10 p.m. daily from Oct. 19 to Nov. 8. The Funderdome will also feature nightly programming like Nintendo Night, Uno Death Match and a costume contest. Go here for a full list of Funderdome programming. 
Go to funfunfunfest.com for tickets, the Nites schedule and more details about the festival. 
Fun Fun Fun Fest Schedule (All times CT and p.m.)
